quran[33]{c,v,t}:
  18,99,"On that day we will let them dash like billows one over another; and there shall be a blast on the trumpet, and we will gather them together in a body"
  18,100,And we will set Hell on that day close before the infidels
  18,101,"Whose eyes were veiled from my warning, and who had no power to hear"
  18,102,"What! do the infidels think that they can take my servants as their patrons, beside Me? Verily, we have got Hell ready as the abode of the infidels"
  18,103,"SAY: Shall we tell you who they are that have lost their labour most"
  18,104,"Whose aim in the present life hath been mistaken, and who deem that what they do is right"
  18,105,"They are those who believe not in the signs of the Lord, or that they shall ever meet him. Vain, therefore, are their works; and no weight will we allow them on the day of resurrection"
  18,106,"This shall be their reward - Hell. Because they were unbelievers, and treated my signs and my Apostles with scorn"
  18,107,"But as for those who believe and do the things that are right, they shall have the gardens of Paradise for their abode"
  18,108,"They shall remain therein for ever: they shall wish for no change from it"
  18,109,"SAY: Should the sea become ink, to write the words of my Lord, the sea would surely fail ere the words of my Lord would fail, though we brought its like in aid"
  18,110,"SAY: In sooth I am only a man like you. It hath been revealed to me that your God is one only God: let him then who hopeth to meet his Lord work a righteous work: nor let him give any other creature a share in the worship of his Lord"
  19,1,KAF. HA. YA. AIN. SAD
  19,2,A recital of thy Lord's mercy to his servant Zachariah
  19,3,When he called upon his Lord with secret calling
  19,4,"And said: \"O Lord, verily my bones are weakened, and the hoar hairs glisten on my head, And never, Lord, have I prayed to thee with ill success"
  19,5,"But now I have fears for my kindred after me; and my wife is barren: Give me, then, a successor as thy special gift"
  19,6,"who shall be my heir and an heir of the family of Jacob: and make him, Lord, well pleasing to thee"
  19,7,"O Zachariah! verily we announce to thee a son, - his name John: That name We have given to none before him"
  19,8,"He said: \"O my Lord! how when my wife is barren shall I have a son, and when I have now reached old age, failing in my powers"
  19,9,"He said: So shall it be. Thy Lord hath said, Easy is this to me, for I created thee aforetime when thou wast nothing"
  19,10,"He said: \"Vouchsafe me, O my Lord! a sign.\" He said: \"Thy sign shall be that for three nights, though sound in health, thou speakest not to man"
  19,11,"And he came forth from the sanctuary to his people, and made signs to them to sing praises morn and even"
  19,12,"We said: \"O John! receive the Book with purpose of heart:\" - and We bestowed on him wisdom while yet a child"
  19,13,"And mercifulness from Ourself, and purity; and pious was he"
  19,14,"and duteous to his parents; and not proud, rebellious"
  19,15,"And peace was on him on the day he was born, and the day of his death, and shall be on the day when he shall be raised to life"
  19,16,"And make mention in the Book, of Mary, when she went apart from her family, eastward"
  19,17,"And took a veil to shroud herself from them: and we sent our spirit to her, and he took before her the form of a perfect man"
  19,18,"She said: \"I fly for refuge from thee to the God of Mercy! If thou fearest Him, begone from me"
  19,19,"He said: \"I am only a messenger of thy Lord, that I may bestow on thee a holy son"
  19,20,"She said: \"How shall I have a son, when man hath never touched me? and I am not unchaste"
  19,21,"He said: \"So shall it be. Thy Lord hath said: 'Easy is this with me;' and we will make him a sign to mankind, and a mercy from us. For it is a thing decreed"